==================
FetchContent Notes
==================

Dependencies downloaded via FetchContent are placed in

    build/_deps/

and are not stored in the repository.

The first CMake configure therefore requires an internet connection.
Subsequent builds are performed using the cached copies.

===============
Structure Notes
===============

Sorcery is organised into the following static libraries:

- sorcery_core
- sorcery_engine
- sorcery_frontend
- sorcery_gui
- sorcery_modules
- sorcery_resources
- sorcery_types
- dear_imgui

These are linked together to produce the final executable.

========
Building
========

Clone the repository:

	git clone https://github.com/davemoore22/sorcery.git

Configure:

	cmake -S . -B build

Compile:

	cmake --build build

or

	cmake --build build --parallel

Output is in the build/dist directory

==========
Post-build
==========

The build automatically creates and copies these directories and their contents:

cfg/
dat/
doc/
gfx/
sav/
sav/characters/
sav/states/
sfx/
vfx/

